   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The voltage limitation unit (VLU) helps to limit the rectifier
DC output voltage in case of a fast increase in the voltage variation
on the rectifier AC mains input. The VLU directly communicates with
the main controller and with the thyristor firing card.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">For the VLU there are multiple conditions and steps to limit the
DC voltage:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">VLU activation setting. Defines at what voltage level the VLU
will activate.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Control pulse blocking. Blocks the next rectifier thyristor
firing pulse with direct communication to the thyristor firing card.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Energy absorption. Lowers the DC voltage if it continues to
rise.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">As an option it is possible to have a switch that can temporarily
deactivate the VLU function. This could be needed if the activation
setting is very low, so that it might trigger if the rectifier charge
mode is initial or boost charge.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The type and placement of the switch depends on customer specifications.
For more details see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Drawings</i>.</p>
